block.documentation:
The Manufacturing Subsystem is central to the AOMS, responsible for the precise and automated production of ZBLAN optical fibers in a microgravity environment. The process begins with the Preform Heater, which melts ZBLAN preforms at controlled high temperatures, ensuring the material reaches a molten state ideal for fiber drawing. The ZBLAN Fiber Drawing Unit then pulls the fiber at a carefully controlled speed, a process made easier by the microgravity conditions, which prevent defects like crystallization or irregularities. The Spool Linear Stage and Spool Tension Motor work in tandem to maintain proper fiber tension as the fiber is drawn and cooled. Tension control is critical to the fiberâ€™s quality, ensuring that it maintains the correct diameter throughout the production process.
This subsystem is highly automated and controlled by the Process Control CSC, a software component responsible for adjusting parameters such as drawing speed, heater temperature, and spool rotation in real-time. The Fiber Annealer cools the fiber gradually, solidifying it without introducing imperfections. The Preform Holder and Heater Stage are critical mechanical elements that ensure the preform is consistently heated and positioned correctly. This integrated system allows for continuous fiber production with minimal human intervention, optimizing both the quantity and quality of the output.
